  "market_context": "Bitcoin was consolidating near a strong resistance zone formed by four pivot points at ~86,800–86,820 on the daily chart. Price had previously tested this level multiple times without breaking it.",
  "key_observation": "A cluster of four pivot points (using 20-20-20 settings) formed a highly significant resistance level; breakout above it triggered a strong bullish move confirmed by net buying volume in the delta footprint.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst applied Pivot Points High/Low indicator with 20-20-20 settings to identify significant swing highs/lows on the BTCUSDT daily chart.",
    "Step 2: He observed four pivot points clustered tightly around 86,800–86,820, forming a strong resistance zone, and drew a horizontal line to mark it.",
    "Step 3: He noted that price broke above this multi-pivot resistance level, followed immediately by a sharp upward rally.",
    "Step 4: He switched to Volume Footprint chart, changed settings to 'Delta', and confirmed the breakout was accompanied by strong net buying volume (green bars), validating the move."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price rallied sharply after the breakout; the analyst noted the level later acted as support with a bounce just above it.",
  "lessons": "Multi-pivot clusters (especially with longer 20-20-20 settings) form high-probability resistance/support zones; breakouts from such levels are most reliable when confirmed by volume delta showing net institutional buying.",
